description: I have a Dell AMD 64 with Ubuntu 18.04 OS running on it. Installed Tensorflow from the app center. After installing, I tried to launch the program but it does not open. Sor for me, the program doesn't work.

One must have preinstalled snap, probably, to work from here. I also have tensor flow and its dependencies installed, and there are a lot. App pulls up 3 images that are basically the tv color test type screen. you can click on the image to have tensor flow analyze and it returns as website screen, but this doesnt do justice to what the app can do. Is source code installed that could be used on a file containing jpegs? I would have to search to find out. But you get the basic idea of how it should work when tensorflow is installed an analysis modules are downloaded and you code an app to include those modules.
